<p>&#8220;40 Years in the Desert,&#8221; a talk I gave at Copycamp in Warsaw, Poland, on November 26 2012. Audio is a bit messed up until 02:49, so just start there. I talk a bit about <a href="http://questioncopyright.org/">Questioncopyright.org</a> and <a href="http://questioncopyright.org/minute_memes">Minute Memes</a>, liberally <a href="http://torrentfreak.com/get-ready-for-another-forty-years-of-corporate-copyright-bullshit-120826/">quote</a> Rick <a href="http://falkvinge.net/">Falkvinge</a>, mention Fair Use and Creative Commons before getting into <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2012/05/12/intellectual-disobedience/">Intellectual Disobedience</a>. Toward the end I discuss <em>Seder-Masochism&#8217;s</em> release plan.</p>
